  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"aphelios","win":["Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Skill","Aphelios","Aphelios"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You spike hardest here: with Q (High Note), E (Beat Drop) and a Passive-empowered auto, you out-poke a weapon-locked Aphelios who has no dash and only one gun-swap to answer. Land E to slow and root-follow, then chunk him whenever he steps up to last-hit, especially if he's on Gravitum or Severum with no range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Even window. Your Encore (R) is a huge lane-changing charm if you and your support commit, but Aphelios's power now scales with which guns he holds rather than a single ult button, so raw stats even out. Bank R for an all-in when he's caught out of position rather than trading blind."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Aphelios pulls ahead. Once he completes Collector or an ADC first item plus lethality, his Calibrum long-range marks and Infernum AoE turn your minion-hugging into a liability. Respect his range and stop walking up for greedy Q pokes."},{"when":"Late","text":"He out-scales you in a straight DPS duel with five guns and a full crit build, so your job is teamfight control. Use Encore and E slows to peel him off your carries and body-block skillshots rather than trying to win a 1v1 auto-attack race."}],"wants":{"you":["Snowball the level 3-6 window with Q/E poke before he itemizes","Land E to lock him for a support-follow all-in","Use minions and range to dodge Calibrum marks"],"foe":["Reach 1-2 items to flip the lane with gun combos","Hold Gravitum/Infernum to zone your walk-ups","Drag the game long into a five-gun crit teamfight"]},"early":"You own levels 1-4. Aphelios has no early mobility and is locked to whatever two guns he loaded, so punish his last-hits with Passive-empowered autos and Q. Keep E up to root-chain any step-up and you can bully him off the wave.","mid":"Levels 3-6 are your peak, but the tide starts turning at 6 as his gun rotations come online. Keep trading on your cooldowns while you're ahead and set up an all-in with your support before he finishes a component; don't over-extend once he can swap into a punishing weapon.","late":"After his first item Aphelios out-duels you outright, so pivot to a utility teamfighter. Shield allies with W, chain E/R to peel, and let your team collapse on him rather than dueling a fully-armed Aphelios.","whys":["You out-poke a locked, immobile Aphelios at level 1 with Passive autos.","Your level 2 spell adds range and a slow he can't match yet.","Level 3 gives you Q, W and E to fully kit-poke before his guns rotate.","Through levels 4-5 he still lacks items so your poke keeps him pinned.","At 6 his gun-based scaling matches your Encore spike, making it even.","One completed item turns his Calibrum/Infernum range against your minion-hugging.","With multiple items his five-gun crit DPS out-duels you outright."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"ashe","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is a pure poke-and-position skill lane. Ashe's Frost Shot slows every auto so she wins prolonged auto exchanges, but your Q (High Note) plus E (Beat Drop) out-range her raw autos and hit harder in short bursts. Whoever lands their spell and steps back cleanly wins each trade, so respect her W (Volley) cone and space behind minions."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Even and dangerous both ways. Ashe's R (Enchanted Crystal Arrow) is a global stun that can set up a support all-in on you, while your Encore charm does the same to her. Track her ult usage; if she fires R and misses, you have a free window to commit E-into-R and burst her down."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Roughly even. Ashe's kite is stronger with an item because Frost Shot perma-slows, but your first-item power (Blackfire Torch / Liandry's or Malignance) lets your abilities chunk her from max range. Trade spells, not autos, and you stay ahead of her sustained DPS."},{"when":"Late","text":"A skill teamfight. Ashe provides slows and a game-winning R engage; you provide charm, shields and AoE burst. Space so her Volley and R can't catch you first, and answer her engage arrow with your own Encore to flip the fight."}],"wants":{"you":["Trade with Q/E spells instead of slowed auto exchanges","Punish a missed Ashe R with an E-Encore all-in","Space behind minions to dodge Volley and arrows"],"foe":["Stack Frost Shot slows to win sustained auto trades","Land a long-range R to set up a support collapse","Kite you in a drawn-out DPS fight"]},"early":"An even, spacing-driven start. Ashe's Frost Shot means she wins slow auto-for-auto trades, so don't sit in her range trading autos; use your longer-range Q and E to poke and back off. Whoever plays the minion line and cooldowns better takes the early edge.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay knife-edge. Keep trading with spells while dodging Volley, and at 6 the lane is decided by ults: her Crystal Arrow can start an all-in on you, but a whiffed arrow gives you a clean E-into-Encore kill window. Ward for her jungler since her R sets up ganks.","late":"Purely skill-based teamfighting. You bring charm, shields and AoE; she brings perma-slows and a global engage. Position so you aren't the first target, peel with E, and use Encore to answer her engage rather than dueling her kite.","whys":["Level 1 is even: her Frost-Shot slow trades against your longer poke range.","Level 2 stays skill-based, first spell landed decides the trade.","At 3 both have full early kits, so cooldown discipline decides it.","Through 4-5 neither pulls ahead without a misplay.","At 6 both ults set up all-ins, keeping the window even.","One item helps her kite but arms your spell-poke equally.","Late fights hinge on positioning and ult trades, not raw stats."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"caitlyn","win":["Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Caitlyn dominates this window. Her 650 auto range plus Headshot procs and Q (Piltover Peacemaker) out-range every one of your spells, so she zones you off the wave and cracks your last-hits under tower. Her E (90 Caliber Net) also traps into her W (Yordle Snap Trap), setting up a support-follow all-in you can't easily escape without Flash."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Still Caitlyn-favoured. Your Encore is a strong charm, but she out-ranges your engage attempts and can burst you before you close the gap; her R (Ace in the Hole) also executes you from afar. Only commit R when your support has hard CC to lock her, otherwise she kites you out."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Caitlyn stays ahead. Her first-item spike (Collector or an early crit item) plus trap-net combos out-trades your spell poke, and her range keeps you hugging minions all game. Farm safely, ward the flanks, and don't step up for greedy Q pokes into her lane bully."},{"when":"Late","text":"Even in a real teamfight. Caitlyn is fragile once you reach her, so your job flips to a utility carry: charm her with Encore, peel with E slows, and shield your frontline. If your team can collapse before she resets Headshots, you can turn the lane deficit around in 5v5."}],"wants":{"you":["Farm safely under tower and scale to teamfights","Punish her only when Net (E) is on cooldown","Reach a full team to collapse on her fragile body"],"foe":["Zone your last-hits with 650 range and Headshot","Trap-Net (W-E) combo into a support all-in","Poke you off the wave every cooldown"]},"early":"Caitlyn hard-bullies the early game. Her superior auto range and Headshot procs zone you off CS, and Peacemaker punishes you when you step up to farm. Take safe last-hits, hug the minion line to block Q, and never walk over a Yordle Snap Trap.","mid":"Levels 3-6 remain her lane. She traps-and-nets into all-ins and out-ranges your spell poke, so play for farm and cooldown windows rather than trades. Even at 6 she out-ranges your Encore engage; only all-in when your support can lock her first, and ward for her aggression.","late":"The matchup evens out in teamfights. Caitlyn folds if you reach her, so pivot to utility: land Encore to charm, chain E slows to peel, and shield allies. Let your frontline engage so you burst her before she kites, turning her lane lead into a neutral 5v5.","whys":["Her 650 range and Headshot zone you off CS at level 1.","Level 2 Headshot poke keeps her firmly ahead.","At 3 her Net-Trap combo out-threatens your kit.","Through 4-5 her range and traps deny your trades.","At 6 she out-ranges your Encore engage and can execute with R.","One item widens her poke and all-in lead over you.","Late, her fragility lets your teamfight utility even the fight."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"corki","win":["Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Skill","Corki","Corki"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You win this window. Corki is weak and mana-hungry early with short auto range, so your Q (High Note) and E (Beat Drop) out-poke him before his item spike. Land E to slow-root and follow with a support all-in whenever he steps up to farm; he has no reliable escape until his W (Valkyrie) is up and mana allows it."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Even. Your Encore charm is a real all-in threat, but Corki's R (Missile Barrage) gives him poke and wave-clear that lets him match your damage from range. Trade spells cleanly and keep E ready; commit R only when he's used W or is out of position."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Corki takes over here. Once he completes his first item and hits the Trinity/Sheen power spike, his true-damage Passive autos and Gatling Gun (E) shred you, and Missile Barrage out-ranges your walk-ups. Stop poking into him and respect his all-in range."},{"when":"Late","text":"Corki out-scales you as a hyper-DPS mid-lane-style carry with true damage and burst. Shift to utility: peel with E slows, charm with Encore, and shield your team with W. Don't duel him; make him fight through your CC while your carries clean up."}],"wants":{"you":["Bully his weak, mana-starved early with Q/E poke","Land E for a support all-in before his item spike","Deny him farm to delay his first item"],"foe":["Complete first item to flip the lane with true damage","Use Missile Barrage range to out-poke your walk-ups","Scale into a hyper-carry with Gatling shred"]},"early":"You control the early game. Corki is squishy, short-ranged and mana-constrained before his items, so poke him with Q and E every time he approaches a minion. A landed E sets up a clean support all-in, and denying his CS meaningfully delays his power spike.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay yours, but the lane levels off at 6 as Missile Barrage gives him range and clear. Keep trading spells on cooldown while you're ahead and look for an Encore all-in when his W is down. Be aware his item spike is coming; don't get caught by the Sheen-empowered burst.","late":"After his first item Corki out-scales you hard with true-damage autos and Gatling Gun. Play utility: chain E slows and Encore to peel, shield with W, and force him to fight through your CC rather than trading autos with a fed hyper-carry.","whys":["Corki's weak, mana-starved level 1 loses to your Passive poke.","Your level 2 spell out-ranges his short early autos.","At 3 your full kit out-trades a mana-hungry Corki.","Through 4-5 he still lacks items so your poke bullies him.","At 6 Missile Barrage's range and clear even the lane.","His first item and true-damage spike flip the lane to him.","Late, his hyper-carry DPS out-scales your duel outright."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"draven","win":["Draven","Draven","Draven","Draven","Draven","Draven","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Draven dominates the early trades. With Spinning Axes (Q) his autos hit for enormous damage and his Passive gold snowballs any lead, so stepping up to trade autos is suicidal. His E (Stand Aside) knocks aside and slows to set up a support all-in, and your squishy body folds if he catches you in range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Still Draven-favoured. Your Encore charm is your best answer, but his R (Whirling Death) executes from across the lane and his League-of-Draven damage lets him all-in you the moment you mispace. Only commit Encore when your support can peel or lock him first."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Draven's spike is brutal. A first-item power buy funded by his Passive bounty lets his axe autos two-to-three-shot you, and his E/all-in threat only grows. Farm from max range, hug your minions, and don't contest the wave when his axes are up."},{"when":"Late","text":"The lane finally evens in teamfights. If Draven drops his axes or gets peeled off, his damage falls off a cliff, so your job is to deny him: charm with Encore, slow with E, and shield your carries. Make him fight through your CC and he loses his tempo."}],"wants":{"you":["Farm safely and deny his axe-catch snowball","Punish only when his Axes (Q) drop","Reach teamfights where CC neutralizes his axes"],"foe":["Snowball early with Spinning Axe auto damage","Land E to set up a support all-in on you","Cash in Passive bounty for a crushing item spike"]},"early":"Draven hard-wins the early game. His Spinning Axe autos out-damage anything you can trade, and his Passive turns every kill into a snowball. Give up contested CS, hug the minion line to avoid his E knock-aside, and farm safely rather than feeding his bounty engine.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay his lane. His all-in with E and axe stacks beats your kit in a straight fight, and at 6 Whirling Death executes you from range. Play for farm and safety, only using Encore when your support can lock him, and ward heavily since he loves diving with a jungler.","late":"Teamfights level the matchup. Draven falls off if his axes drop or he's peeled, so pivot fully to utility: Encore to charm, E to slow, W to shield. Don't duel him; force him to fight through CC while your team punishes his mispositioning.","whys":["Draven's Spinning-Axe autos out-damage your level 1 trades.","His axe damage and Passive gold snowball level 2.","At 3 his E all-in threat beats your kit.","Through 4-5 his bounty-funded lead keeps him ahead.","At 6 Whirling Death executes you from range.","His first-item spike lets axes nearly two-shot you.","Late, CC-heavy teamfights finally neutralize his axes."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"ezreal","win":["Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Skill","Ezreal","Ezreal"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You win the early trades. Ezreal is weak before items and relies on landing Mystic Shot (Q) to trade; if he misses, he takes your Q and E for free. Your poke out-damages his early autos, and a landed E (Beat Drop) sets up a support all-in he can only escape with a charge of E (Arcane Shift). Bait his E, then commit."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Even. Your Encore charm is strong, but Ezreal's R (Trueshot Barrage) adds burst and his E blink makes him slippery, so raw kill pressure evens out. Trade Q/E poke, track his Arcane Shift cooldown, and only all-in when his blink is down."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Ezreal pulls ahead. His first-item spike (Manamune into Trinity/tear stacks) makes Mystic Shot hurt and his mana problems vanish, so he pokes you from safety and out-sustains your trades. Respect his Q range and stop stepping up for greedy pokes."},{"when":"Late","text":"Ezreal out-scales you with safe, high-range poke and constant E repositioning. Pivot to utility: charm with Encore, slow with E, and shield your team with W. You can't chase a blinking Ezreal, so make your team collapse when he blinks in, and peel rather than duel."}],"wants":{"you":["Punish missed Mystic Shots with Q/E poke","Bait his Arcane Shift, then land E for an all-in","Deny his tear/Manamune stacks early"],"foe":["Complete Manamune to solve mana and spike poke","Use Arcane Shift to dodge your E and kite","Scale into safe long-range poke teamfights"]},"early":"You control the early game. Ezreal is item-reliant and punishable when he whiffs Mystic Shot, so trade your poke into his missed skillshots and hug minions to avoid his Q. Landing E sets up a support all-in unless he burns Arcane Shift, so bait the blink first.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay yours, evening out at 6. Keep punishing missed Qs and look for an Encore all-in when his E is down, but respect that Trueshot Barrage and his blink give him outs. Deny his tear stacks by winning trades so his first-item spike arrives later.","late":"After Manamune Ezreal out-pokes and out-sustains you from safety, and his blink makes him impossible to pin. Play utility: Encore to charm, E to peel, W to shield, and collapse as a team when he Arcane Shifts in rather than trying to duel him.","whys":["Ezreal's item-reliant, punishable level 1 loses to your poke.","Your level 2 spell punishes his missed Mystic Shots.","At 3 your full kit out-trades a mana-starved Ezreal.","Through 4-5 he still lacks items so your poke stays ahead.","At 6 his R burst and blink even out the kill pressure.","Manamune solves his mana and spikes his poke past yours.","Late, safe long-range poke and constant blinks out-scale you."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"heimerdinger","win":["Heimerdinger","Heimerdinger","Heimerdinger","Heimerdinger","Skill","Seraphine","Seraphine"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Heimer's H-28G Evolution Turrets zone the wave and chunk you every time you step up to CS, so use your Q High Note poke from max range and only walk in when his turrets are firing at minions, not you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R Encore is a huge equalizer: a wide charm-and-slow that catches Heimer stapled to his turret field lets your support follow up, and it reaches past his W Hextech Micro-Rockets range."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once your first item lands you out-range his effective poke with layered Q and E Beat Drop slows, threatening a real all-in that his squishy turret-reliant kit can't kite away from."},{"when":"Late","text":"In teamfights his turret carpet and R-upgraded abilities matter less than your AoE shield/heal and Encore chaining through his backline as a support-carry hybrid."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 6 with your R Encore up to punish his turret setup","Poke him off his turret field with layered Q Passive-empowered autos","Sidestep his E Beat Drop stun bomb before committing"],"foe":["Freeze the wave behind a wall of Evolution Turrets to deny your CS","Land his skillshot E stun to chunk you with turrets + W rockets","Keep the lane short so his turrets punish every last-hit you take"]},"early":"Heimerdinger dominates levels 1-4: his turret field out-trades your low base damage, zones you off the wave, and punishes any step-up with W rockets, so play safe, CS from range, and don't force trades into his turrets.","mid":"Through 3-5 you're still behind his turret zoning, but once you hit 6 your Encore charm flips the lane -- it catches him pinned to his turrets and, with support CC, converts into a kill his mobility-light kit can't escape.","late":"With items and ults your AoE utility, Notes-empowered range, and Encore chain-CC outscale his stationary turret damage, and you shield/heal your team through his poke while spacing behind minions.","whys":["Heimer's Evolution Turrets out-zone and out-trade your weak level-1 auto damage.","At level 2 his turret field plus W rockets punish any step-up you make.","Level 3 gives him full turret uptime that walls you off the wave.","Through 4-5 his layered turret damage still denies your CS and trades.","Level 6 is even: your Encore counters his ult setup as much as his upgraded turrets threaten you.","With your first item your range and Encore all-in overtake his stationary poke.","Late game your AoE utility and chain-CC outscale his turret-bound damage."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"jhin","win":["Jhin","Jhin","Jhin","Skill","Skill","Jhin","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Jhin's W Deadly Flourish roots you if your support or a minion already tagged you, and his 4th-shot crit blows up trades, so respect his reload window -- when he's on his 4th bullet or reloading, that's your gap to step up and Q poke."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R Encore charm out-ranges and out-CCs his R Curtain Call, but his ult sniping into your positioning is a real threat; use Encore reactively to peel or catch him mid-reload rather than trading ults blindly."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Jhin's first-item damage on his empowered autos and W root spikes hard; play behind minions to break his W line of sight and only commit with your E Beat Drop slow lined up."},{"when":"Late","text":"Teamfights even out: your AoE shield/heal and Encore chain-CC counter his pick-oriented burst, so peel for yourself and body-block his fourth shot from reaching your carries."}],"wants":{"you":["Step up during Jhin's reload/4th-shot window to poke with Q","Break his W Deadly Flourish line of sight behind minions","Land Encore reactively to peel his R Curtain Call snipes"],"foe":["Land W Deadly Flourish root off a support poke or minion damage","Hit the empowered 4th crit shot to win short trades","Snipe your positioning from range with R Curtain Call"]},"early":"Jhin out-trades you levels 1-3: his W root threat, first-shot range, and burst 4th bullet punish you if you step up carelessly, so farm from range, track his reload, and don't stand in W range after taking chip damage.","mid":"By levels 4-6 the lane evens to a skill matchup -- you can dodge his W and punish his reloads, and your Encore charm matches his ult, so trades come down to who lands their key cooldown first.","late":"With items his empowered autos and W root spike again, but late teamfights are even: your AoE utility and reactive Encore CC neutralize his pick threat as long as you space behind your frontline.","whys":["Jhin's long-range first shot and W threat beat your weak level-1 trade.","At level 2 his burst and root setup punish any step-up.","Level 3 gives him full W root + 4th-shot combo pressure over you.","By level 4 it's even -- you can dodge W and abuse his reloads.","Level 5 stays skill-based as your Encore threat matures against his ult.","First item re-spikes his empowered damage and W root over you.","Late game evens out: your AoE peel and CC answer his pick burst."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"jinx","win":["Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Jinx","Jinx"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Jinx is immobile and short-ranged on her Pow-Pow minigun early, so you out-poke her with Q High Note and E Beat Drop slows before she can get rockets rolling -- punish every last-hit she reaches for."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R Encore charm-and-slow gives you a hard all-in Jinx has no escape from; with support CC she can't kite in her rocket stance, and you burst her before Get Excited resets fuel her."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Jinx's first item plus her Fishbones rocket range starts to flip lane control -- respect her Switcheroo poke and W Zap slow, and stop diving her once she can zone with rockets."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late she's one of the best hypercarries: her rocket range and attack-speed resets outrange your damage, so pivot to shielding/healing your own carry and using Encore to peel divers off her, not to trade."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke and all-in her while she's immobile before rocket range online","Land Encore + support CC for an all-in she can't escape","Punish her short minigun range at every last-hit early"],"foe":["Get her Fishbones rockets and W Zap online to zone you out","Snowball off Get Excited resets after a kill or turret","Reach 2+ items where her range and DPS outscale yours"]},"early":"You own levels 1-3: Jinx is immobile and stuck on short minigun range, so your Q poke and E slow chunk her every time she steps to CS, and any all-in with your support favors you hard before her rockets come online.","mid":"Through levels 4-6 you keep the edge -- your Encore all-in punishes her lack of mobility and, with CC, kills her before she kites, so keep denying her farm and deny the Get Excited snowball.","late":"Once Jinx hits her item spikes she outscales you: her Fishbones range, W Zap slow, and reset-fueled DPS overtake your damage, so swap to a peel role, shield your carry, and Encore divers off her.","whys":["Jinx is immobile with short minigun range, so your level-1 poke wins.","At level 2 your Q/E poke keeps chunking her as she steps to farm.","Level 3 gives you a slow-into-all-in she has no escape from.","Through 4-5 your Encore threat and support CC still deny her.","At 6 your full Encore all-in punishes her lack of mobility.","With her first item her rocket range and Zap flip lane control.","Late game her range and reset DPS hard-outscale your damage."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"kaisa","win":["Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Skill","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Kai'Sa is weak and short-ranged before her passive Plasma stacks build, so out-poke her with Q High Note and layer E Beat Drop slows -- every point of poke delays her item spikes and punishes her low early range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R Killer Instinct gives her a dash-in all-in, but your Encore charm out-ranges and interrupts it; hold Encore to peel her engage and, with support CC, punish her the moment she blinks onto you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Kai'Sa spikes hard on her first item's Q evolve and passive plasma detonations -- once she can proc plasma and reset her range, stop stepping up and respect her burst-and-dash pattern."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late she's a mobile burst carry with R repositioning and evolved W/Q; your damage can't chase her, so pivot to shielding your carry and Encore-peeling her all-in, not dueling."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke her down before her Plasma stacks and evolves come online","Interrupt her R Killer Instinct dive with Encore + support CC","Punish her short early range at every last-hit"],"foe":["Stack passive Plasma to detonate burst on you","Evolve Q and W on her first item to spike her range and damage","Use R Killer Instinct to dash in and all-in once ahead"]},"early":"You control levels 1-4: Kai'Sa is short-ranged and fragile before her evolves, so your Q poke and E slows chunk her at every last-hit and delay her scaling, while any support all-in favors you before her R comes online.","mid":"Level 6 is a skill window -- her R dive threatens you but your Encore charm interrupts it, so trades come down to whether you land CC on her blink or she bursts you with a plasma detonation first.","late":"After her first item Kai'Sa outscales you: evolved abilities, plasma burst, and R repositioning let her all-in and escape your damage, so shift to peel, shield your carry, and save Encore for her dive.","whys":["Kai'Sa's short early range loses to your level-1 poke.","At level 2 your Q/E poke keeps her off the wave and behind.","Level 3 lets you slow-and-trade her fragile early kit.","Through level 4-5 your poke still delays her evolves and farm.","Level 6 is even -- her R dive is countered by your Encore interrupt.","Her first-item evolves spike her range and burst over you.","Late game her mobility and plasma burst hard-outscale your damage."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"kalista","win":["Kalista","Kalista","Kalista","Kalista","Kalista","Kalista","Seraphine"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Kalista's Hop passive lets her dance in and out of your Q and E while stacking spears with Pierce, so she out-trades you constantly -- don't try to CS while she has her support up, and only step in when her spears are on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R Fate's Call gives her and her support a re-engage/disengage tool that dodges your Encore, and she can bait your ult; hold Encore for when she commits Hop distance and can't reposition out of the charm."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Kalista's first item ramps her spear stacking and Rend burst -- her mobility means she kites your slows freely, so play behind minions, farm safe, and don't get chunked by ranged Pierce poke."},{"when":"Late","text":"Only in the very late game do your AoE utility and Encore chain-CC pull ahead -- her single-target Rend and Hop kiting matter less in 5v5 than your team-wide shield/heal and a clutch Encore into her backline."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach late game where your AoE utility outscales her single-target kite","Land Encore when she over-commits her Hop distance","Farm safe behind minions and dodge her Pierce poke"],"foe":["Kite your Q and E freely with her Hop passive","Stack spears and burst with Rend in extended trades","Use R Fate's Call to dodge Encore and re-engage"]},"early":"Kalista bullies levels 1-5: her Hop passive lets her dodge your Q and E while stacking spears and poking with Pierce, so she wins every extended trade -- give up contested CS, farm safe, and never fight into her mobility.","mid":"Through level 6 she stays ahead -- her R Fate's Call dodges your Encore and enables re-engages, and her Rend burst punishes any misstep, so keep playing behind minions and only look for a pick when her Hop is committed.","late":"Only at 2+ items does the matchup flip to you: your AoE shield/heal and Encore chain-CC outvalue her single-target kiting in teamfights, so peel for your carry and land Encore when she dives in.","whys":["Kalista's Hop passive dodges your poke and wins level-1 trades.","At level 2 she kites your Q/E and stacks spears freely.","Level 3 Rend burst punishes any trade you attempt.","Through 4-5 her mobility and Pierce poke keep her ahead.","Level 6 R Fate's Call dodges Encore and re-engages on you.","First item ramps her spear-stack Rend burst over you.","Late game your AoE utility and chain-CC finally outscale her kite."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"karthus","win":["Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Skill","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Karthus is immobile and relies on landing Q Lay Waste, so early you out-poke him with your own longer-uptime Q and E slows -- step up when his Q is on cooldown and punish his fragile, mobility-less body at every last-hit."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His R Requiem is global execute pressure but doesn't win lane trades; the danger is his E Defile ramping AoE and passive Death Defiance, so respect his zone -- his level 6 shifts the matchup toward him as his AP scaling comes online."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Karthus's first AP item makes his Q Lay Waste last-hit poke and E Defile aura genuinely threatening, and his passive lets him keep dealing damage after death -- stop trading into his ramping AoE and farm from range."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late he outscales you as an AoE mage-carry: layered Lay Waste, Defile zoning, and global Requiem burst overtake your damage, so pivot to shielding your team and using Encore to peel or catch him before he free-casts."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke his immobile body while his Q is on cooldown early","All-in him before his AP scaling and Defile come online","Punish every last-hit he reaches for with Q and E"],"foe":["Ramp AP so Q Lay Waste and E Defile become real threats","Use passive Death Defiance to keep dealing damage post-death","Zone teamfights with Defile aura and global Requiem burst"]},"early":"You win levels 1-3: Karthus is immobile and depends on landing Lay Waste, so your longer-uptime Q poke and E slow out-trade him and punish his fragile early body whenever his Q is down.","mid":"Level 4 is even, then the lane tilts to Karthus at 6 -- his E Defile aura, R Requiem pressure, and passive Death Defiance make trading into him costly as his AP scaling comes online, so stop diving and farm safe.","late":"With items Karthus outscales you: his ramping Lay Waste, Defile zoning, and global Requiem burst overtake your damage, so shift to shielding your carry and Encore-peeling him before he free-casts in fights.","whys":["Karthus is immobile and Q-reliant, so your level-1 poke wins.","At level 2 your Q/E out-trade his fragile early body.","Level 3 lets you all-in him before his AP scaling arrives.","Level 4 is even as his Defile and your poke balance out.","Level 6 tilts to him: Requiem and Death Defiance grow his threat.","First AP item makes his Lay Waste and Defile out-damage you.","Late game his AoE zoning and global burst hard-outscale you."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"kogmaw","win":["Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Kog'Maw","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"With Q, W and E online you own the poke war: E Beat Drop slows Kog'Maw and your Q High Note hits for a chunk since he has no dash to sidestep it, letting you shove and pressure his low-mobility body under tower."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Encore is a huge lane-ending all-in here; if you or your support land any prior CC, the charm connects and a low-range Kog'Maw has no escape, so pair R with your support's engage."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Kog'Maw's first item (often on-hit like Guinsoo's/Nashor's or Manamune) is where his DPS jumps; his W-shredding auto range starts to out-range your safe poke."},{"when":"Late","text":"In teamfights a peeled Kog'Maw with W active melts you and your team from max range; you must play to burst him before his ult-fueled DPS ramps."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke him down with Q while he can't dash away from your E slow","Land Encore off any support CC before he buys range items","Perma-shove so he last-hits under tower and eats harass"],"foe":["Reach on-hit first item to out-range your poke","Get a peeling support so his W DPS ramps safely","Drag the game to full build where his ult and range dominate"]},"early":"You dominate levels 1-5: Kog'Maw is one of the least mobile ADCs, so your E Beat Drop reliably slows him and your Q High Note lands for free while he has no dash to dodge. Shove the wave and force him to last-hit under tower where he soaks your poke.","mid":"Through level 6 you stay ahead. Your Encore is a lane-ending threat because Kog'Maw cannot flash-dash out of a charm chain, so coordinate R with any support hard-CC for an all-in. Keep whittling his HP with Q before he completes an item.","late":"Once Kog'Maw finishes his first on-hit item the matchup flips: his W-shredded, ramping auto range out-ranges your poke and his ult passive lets him bully you at max distance. At two-plus items you must burst him fast in fights or he deletes your backline before you kite.","whys":["You win level 1: Kog'Maw has no early trading tools and can't escape your auto poke.","You win level 2: adding a second ability lets you zone his immobile body off farm.","You win level 3: full Q-W-E kit lets you slow with E and land guaranteed Q poke.","You win levels 4-5: your poke and E slow keep a dashless Kog'Maw pinned under tower.","You win level 6: Encore is an unstoppable all-in on a champion with zero escape.","Kog'Maw wins first item: his on-hit spike out-ranges and out-DPSes your safe poke.","Kog'Maw wins 2+ items: full-build range and W shred let him melt you before you can kite."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"lucian","win":["Lucian","Lucian","Lucian","Lucian","Lucian","Lucian","Seraphine"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Lucian's Piercing Light (Q) plus Relentless Pursuit (E) dash lets him weave in double-auto Passive procs and dash out before your E Beat Drop lands, punishing every step you take to farm."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Encore is your one real answer, but Lucian's E dash and any Lucian-Nami/Braum tempo means he can dash out of the charm windup; you need CC set up first."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Lucian spikes hard at his first item (typically Essence Reaver/Kraken plus Boots) and his lane-bully double-auto pattern outraces your enchanter DPS."},{"when":"Late","text":"By two-plus items you out-scale: your Q High Note, teamfight shields/heals and Encore across a grouped fight let you swing 5v5s a hyper-Lucian can't."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive lane and scale to your two-item teamfight power","Land Encore only after support locks him so his E can't dodge","Use W shields to eat his double-auto burst and reset trades"],"foe":["Abuse his Q-E-Passive combo to win every short trade","Snowball his first-item spike before you come online","Dash with E to dodge your Beat Drop and all-in windups"]},"early":"Lucian bullies you from level 1: his double-auto Lightslinger passive and Piercing Light out-trade your enchanter kit, and Relentless Pursuit lets him dash in for a combo then dash out before your E Beat Drop or Q can punish. Play behind minions and only step up for safe last-hits.","mid":"Through level 6 he stays ahead. Your Encore is the only tool that flips a trade, but Lucian's E dash dodges the windup unless your support lands hard CC first, so hold R for a set-up all-in and otherwise farm defensively with W to soak his burst.","late":"The matchup inverts at two-plus items. Lucian falls off relative to scaling carries while your Q High Note, grouped shields and heals, and a fight-swinging Encore give you 5v5 control he can't match. Play safe, hit your item spikes, and win through teamfighting.","whys":["Lucian wins level 1: his double-auto passive out-trades your weak early kit.","Lucian wins level 2: Piercing Light plus autos punish you before your abilities online.","Lucian wins level 3: full Q-E-Passive combo lets him dash in and out of your range.","Lucian wins levels 4-5: his mobility dodges your E and sustains lane dominance.","Lucian wins level 6: his E dash sidesteps your Encore windup without set-up CC.","Lucian wins first item: his early-item spike out-damages your enchanter curve.","You win 2+ items: your scaling teamfight kit and Encore out-value a falloff Lucian."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"missfortune","win":["Miss Fortune","Miss Fortune","Miss Fortune","Skill","Miss Fortune","Miss Fortune","Seraphine"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Miss Fortune's Double Up (Q) bounces off minions or you for big poke and her Love Tap passive punishes you every time you swap targets to farm; at level 4-5 it evens out as your Q-W-E poke-and-shield trades back."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Bullet Time is a lane-deleting ult; if her support lands CC she can channel on top of you, so respect her all-in and use W move speed or E to break line of sight."},{"when":"1st item","text":"MF's first item plus her Q reset pattern keeps her poke lead, out-ranging your safe harass and forcing you off the wave."},{"when":"Late","text":"You out-scale into two items: your Q High Note, grouped shields/heals and an Encore that can cancel her Bullet Time channel swing late fights your way."}],"wants":{"you":["Stack HP/positioning so her Double Up can't bounce onto you","Save Encore to interrupt her Bullet Time channel in fights","Reach two items where your teamfight kit overtakes her poke"],"foe":["Poke with Q bounces and Love Tap resets every trade","Land a full Bullet Time channel on a clumped lane","Snowball her early-item poke lead before you scale"]},"early":"Miss Fortune out-pokes you from level 1: Double Up bounces off the caster minion or a nearby target for heavy damage, and her Love Tap passive taxes you every time you switch to last-hit. Stand so the Q can't ricochet onto you and only step up for safe CS behind the wave.","mid":"Level 4-5 evens out (Skill) as your full Q-W-E kit lets you shield the poke and trade back, but by level 6 respect Bullet Time: with any support CC she can channel on top of you for a kill. Break her channel line of sight with W's move speed or an E slow and don't clump with your support.","late":"You take over at two-plus items. Your Q High Note, grouped shields and heals, and most importantly an Encore that can charm-cancel her Bullet Time channel let you swing teamfights she used to win with poke. Play to group and fight rather than trade autos.","whys":["Miss Fortune wins level 1: Double Up poke and Love Tap out-trade your early kit.","Miss Fortune wins level 2: her Q bounce zones you off farm before you online.","Miss Fortune wins level 3: sustained Double Up harass keeps her poke lead.","Even at levels 4-5: your full Q-W-E poke-and-shield lets you trade back skillfully.","Miss Fortune wins level 6: Bullet Time is a lane-deleting all-in with support CC.","Miss Fortune wins first item: her early poke spike keeps you off the wave.","You win 2+ items: your teamfight kit and channel-cancel Encore out-scale her poke."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"nilah","win":["Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Nilah","Nilah","Nilah"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Nilah is a melee ADC, so at levels 3-5 you abuse range: E Beat Drop slows her approach and Q High Note pokes her every time she walks up to CS, forcing her to farm at max whip range or take free damage."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Nilah spikes at 6 with Apotheosis; her W Jubilant Veil dodges your Q and she can Slipstream (E) dash onto you, so her all-in threat now beats your poke lane."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After her first item Nilah's healing and shared-XP execution damage let her survive your poke and burst you the moment she closes the gap."},{"when":"Late","text":"Nilah's Lasso ult pulls your whole team in and her lifesteal-sharing lets her ADC-carry fights; a melee she now out-sustains and out-teamfights your enchanter body."}],"wants":{"you":["Zone her off CS with Q poke while she's stuck in melee range","Slow her walk-up with E so she never trades evenly","Punish her low early range before she hits level 6"],"foe":["Reach level 6 Apotheosis and W-dodge your poke","Dash in with Slipstream and all-in once she has sustain","Group for Lasso teamfights where her lifesteal-sharing shines"]},"early":"You bully Nilah levels 1-4 because she is a melee ADC with a short whip range: every time she steps up to last-hit, your Q High Note pokes her and your E Beat Drop slows her retreat. Hold the wave near your side and make her choose between farming and taking chip damage.","mid":"The lane flips at level 6 (Nilah). Apotheosis powers up her kit, W Jubilant Veil lets her dodge your Q and empowered autos, and Slipstream dashes her onto you for an all-in your poke can no longer keep out. Play safer, respect her gap-close, and use W move speed to disengage.","late":"Nilah out-scales you at items. Her lifesteal-sharing keeps her ADC and support topped through your poke, and her Lasso ult pulls your backline into her team's follow-up. A melee that used to fear your range now out-sustains and out-teamfights you, so peel hard and burst her before she locks the fight.","whys":["You win level 1: Nilah's melee range lets you poke her for free as she CSes.","You win level 2: your added ability zones her short-range body off farm.","You win level 3: full Q-E kit slows and pokes her every walk-up.","You win levels 4-5: range advantage keeps a melee Nilah eating chip damage.","Nilah wins level 6: Apotheosis, W dodge and Slipstream flip the all-in her way.","Nilah wins first item: her sustain survives your poke and enables her dive.","Nilah wins 2+ items: lifesteal-sharing and Lasso out-teamfight your enchanter kit."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"samira","win":["Samira","Samira","Samira","Samira","Samira","Samira","Seraphine"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Samira's Wild Rush (E) dash through minions plus her blade-range Q lets her weave in style-stacking damage and dash out before your E Beat Drop lands, punishing you for stepping up."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Inferno Trigger is a lane-ending execute once she hits S-rank; her W can also block your Q and Encore projectiles, so never all-in without hard CC pinning her first."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Samira snowballs off her first item; her dash-heavy trades and W windwall keep her ahead of your enchanter DPS and shields."},{"when":"Late","text":"You out-scale into two items: from range your Q High Note, grouped shields/heals and a set-up Encore let you burst her before she can start her dash-reset ult chain."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive lane and scale to your two-item teamfight power","Never Q or Encore into her raised W windwall","Land Encore only after support locks her dash down"],"foe":["Abuse Wild Rush dashes to trade and escape your slows","Reach S-rank for a lane-ending Inferno Trigger","Snowball her first-item spike before you come online"]},"early":"Samira bullies you from level 1: her Wild Rush dash lets her burst in for style-stacking damage and dash back out before your E Beat Drop or Q can catch her, and her melee-range Q punishes your walk-ups. Farm from max range behind your minions and refuse to trade into her mobility.","mid":"She stays ahead through level 6. Inferno Trigger executes a lane at S-rank, and her W windwall blocks your Q and Encore projectiles, so any all-in you attempt needs your support to hard-CC her dash first. Otherwise soak trades with W shields and give up unsafe CS.","late":"The matchup inverts at two-plus items. From safe range your Q High Note, grouped shields and heals, and a set-up Encore let you lock and burst Samira before she can start her dash-and-reset ult chain. Play safe early, hit your item spikes, and win the fight before she gets rolling.","whys":["Samira wins level 1: her dash-in burst out-trades your fragile early kit.","Samira wins level 2: Wild Rush mobility punishes every step you take to CS.","Samira wins level 3: full Q-E combo lets her trade and escape your slows.","Samira wins levels 4-5: her dashes dodge your E and sustain lane control.","Samira wins level 6: Inferno Trigger executes and W blocks your all-in.","Samira wins first item: her early snowball spike out-damages your curve.","You win 2+ items: your ranged teamfight kit and set-up Encore out-value her."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"senna","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Senna"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is a poke mirror: Senna's Piercing Darkness (Q) heals and pokes at range while your Q High Note and E slow trade back, so the lane is decided by who lands skillshots and dodges better, not levels."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Both ults reach the fight from afar; her global Dawning Shadow shields her team while your Encore charms, so it stays even and comes down to which ult swings the skirmish."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Senna's soul-stacking scales her range and crit, but at one item the poke war is still roughly even if you respect her Q range and keep shielding the chip."},{"when":"Late","text":"Senna out-scales hard: stacked souls give her absurd range, crit and lifesteal, and her global ult out-values your enchanter kit across the map."}],"wants":{"you":["Win the skillshot-dodging poke war with Q and E","Shield your support and yourself to negate her Q chip","Force fights before her soul stacks snowball her range"],"foe":["Farm souls freely to scale range, crit and lifesteal","Poke and heal with Q to out-sustain the lane","Drag the game late where stacked Senna dominates"]},"early":"Levels 1-5 are a pure skill matchup (Skill): both of you are ranged pokers, so it comes down to landing Q High Note versus her Piercing Darkness and dodging each other's skillshots. Use E Beat Drop to punish her when she steps up for a soul, and shield the chip damage so neither side gets a clean lead.","mid":"Level 6 stays even. Her global Dawning Shadow can shield her team from across the map while your Encore charms a clumped enemy, so skirmishes hinge on which ult you land better, not on a raw power gap. Keep contesting her souls to slow her scaling.","late":"Senna pulls ahead at two-plus items because her soul stacking is relentless: she gains huge attack range, crit and lifesteal, and her global ult keeps out-valuing your enchanter kit. Your best window is forcing objective fights before her stacks pile up, because late she simply out-ranges and out-scales you.","whys":["Even at level 1: both are ranged pokers deciding the lane on skillshots.","Even at level 2: the poke-and-dodge mirror still comes down to execution.","Even at level 3: your Q and E trade evenly with her Piercing Darkness poke.","Even at levels 4-5: shielding the chip keeps the poke war balanced.","Even at level 6: both global-reach ults make skirmishes a skill test.","Even at first item: the poke lane stays roughly balanced with good spacing.","Senna wins 2+ items: stacked souls give her range, crit and scaling you can't match."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"sivir","win":["Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Skill","Sivir","Sivir"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Your Q poke plus a shielded/hasted E on your support out-trades Sivir before she has the mana or waveclear to punch back; every time she Q-boomerangs the wave you can walk up and land free Q harass while she has no threat back."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Both of you hit a teamfight ult at once: your Encore chains off any minion or champ for a huge chain-CC, but Sivir's R (On The Hunt) gives her lane the movespeed to sidestep your skillshots and reposition, so the level becomes about who lands their AoE first."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sivir spikes hard at one item because her Q with Spellblade waveclears instantly and her E Spell Shield can eat your Q or a support engage, flipping the wave and denying your poke windows."},{"when":"Late","text":"With Spell Shield up permanently and her ult buffing the whole team's kiting, Sivir out-positions you in 5v5; you must land Encore from fog or off a tank's engage before she blocks and dashes the fight away."}],"wants":{"you":["Long-range Q poke chunks before she trades back","A support with lockdown CC so your Encore chains onto a caught target","Short lane trades while her Q boomerang is on cooldown"],"foe":["Reaching one completed item so Spellblade Q shoves and clears your poke","Baiting your Q or engage into her E Spell Shield","Teamfights where On The Hunt lets her team kite your slow skillshots"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are yours: your Q outranges Sivir's auto-harass and her early mana pool can't sustain a poke war, so shield your support with E and keep landing Q while she's forced to farm.","mid":"Through 4-5 you stay ahead on poke and can force short trades whenever her Q is down, but respect that at 6 her On The Hunt buys her lane the speed to dodge your Encore and rotate.","late":"Once Sivir completes her first item she flips the lane with Spellblade waveclear and a reliable Spell Shield, and in full teamfights her ult's movespeed lets her team dodge your telegraphed AoE, so you rely on catching her off-guard from fog.","whys":["At level 1 your Q outranges Sivir's autos so early harass favours you.","Level 2 your extra shield or Q point keeps you winning the poke exchange.","At level 3 short trades on her Q cooldown still favour your damage.","Through 4-5 your sustained Q poke keeps chunking her before she itemizes.","At 6 both ults swing the fight so the level is even and skill-dependent.","At one item Sivir's Spellblade waveclear and Spell Shield tip the lane to her.","With items and On The Hunt Sivir out-kites and blocks your poke in fights."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"smolder","win":["Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Smolder is a scaling stack-champ who is weak and short-ranged early, so your Q outranges his Super Scorcher Breath and you can chunk him every time he walks up to last-hit, denying the stacks he desperately needs."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Encore is a lane-winning AoE root/dance that chains through his minions onto him, and since he has few stacks and no escape yet, a 6 all-in with support CC can simply delete him before he threatens back."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Smolder's whole gameplan is item and stack timing; at one component-heavy item his Q starts doing real single-target damage and his W executes low minions to farm safely, so his kill pressure begins to flip toward him."},{"when":"Late","text":"Once Smolder has stacks and items his empowered Q and dragon ult (R) outrange and out-DPS you from a screen away; you must burst him with Encore before he ramps or he kites your team down."}],"wants":{"you":["Punishing his weak early range before he stacks","All-in windows at 3-6 while he has no escape and low stacks","A support with hard CC to guarantee an Encore all-in"],"foe":["Farming safely to 225 stacks with W executes","Reaching item and stack thresholds so his Q one-shots waves and you","Late fights where his ranged R and empowered Q kite from max range"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are firmly yours: Smolder is one of the weakest early laners, so hold priority with Q poke, shield your support, and freeze him off farm to starve his stacks.","mid":"Through 3-6 you own every window, using Q harass on his last-hits and a 6 Encore all-in with support CC to punish a champion who has no escape and little stack payoff yet.","late":"After his first item and stack milestones Smolder overtakes you hard, his empowered Q and dragon ult outrange everything you have, so your only path is to snowball the early lead and blow him up before he comes online.","whys":["Level 1 Smolder is extremely weak so your Q harass dominates.","Level 2 your poke and shield keep pressuring his fragile early kit.","At level 3 you out-trade a short-ranged, stackless Smolder easily.","Through 4-5 you keep starving his stacks with priority and poke.","At 6 your Encore all-in punishes his lack of escape and low stacks.","At one item Smolder's ramping Q damage flips kill pressure to him.","With stacks and items Smolder out-ranges and out-DPSes you in fights."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"swain","win":["Swain","Swain","Swain","Swain","Swain","Swain","Seraphine"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Swain bot bullies you with his W root-vision and Q burst; his Nevermove (E) pull plus a support engage threatens to root you the moment you step up for a last-hit, so play behind your caster minions and never trade into his E."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Swain's Demonic Ascension (R) turns every extended fight into sustain and AoE damage; if he lands E and pops ult on you in lane he out-damages and heals through your Q poke, so avoid committing without a numbers or CC advantage."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With one item Swain's Q and passive soul stacks give him a durable, high-damage frontline profile that shrugs off your poke, and his E pull remains a constant all-in threat that punishes any positioning mistake."},{"when":"Late","text":"Seraphine takes over the late game: from max range your Q and Encore let you poke and chain-CC Swain's whole team before he can close, and if he dives in on ult you disengage while your team collapses on the rooted target."}],"wants":{"you":["Reaching late-game range where your Q and R outclass his","Staying behind minions so his E pull can't connect","Teamfights where your Encore chains off his engage attempt"],"foe":["Landing Nevermove E to lock you for a support all-in","Extended lane trades where his R sustain out-heals your poke","One-item soul-stack durability that eats your early harass"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 already favour Swain: his W harass and looming E pull mean you must respect every step forward, so give ground, farm safely behind your caster minions, and shield preemptively.","mid":"Through 3-6 Swain holds the kill threat with E-into-support-CC and his ult's sustain in extended trades, so you focus on farming to items and only trading Q when his E is on cooldown.","late":"The lane inverts once items and levels are in: your Encore and long Q let you poke and chain-CC from a range Swain can't answer, and you kite his ult dive while your team punishes anyone he tries to pull.","whys":["Level 1 Swain's W harass and E threat put you on the back foot.","Level 2 his pull-plus-engage kill setup keeps the lane his.","At level 3 Swain out-trades you with burst and root pressure.","Through 4-5 his E all-in threat and durability keep you farming safe.","At 6 his R sustain wins extended fights so the level favours him.","At one item Swain's soul-stack tankiness shrugs off your poke.","Late your superior range and Encore chain-CC finally overtake Swain."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"tristana","win":["Tristana","Tristana","Tristana","Tristana","Tristana","Tristana","Tristana"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Tristana's Rocket Jump (W) plus Explosive Charge (E) is a constant all-in threat on your immobile frame; the moment she has W up she can leap onto you and detonate stacked E for a huge burst, so you must stay max-range and never be caught without your support's peel."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her Buster Shot (R) both executes you at the end of a combo and knocks back any support trying to peel, so a level-6 W-E-auto-R sequence can kill you outright; do not step up when her W and R are both available."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Tristana's first-item AD spike massively boosts her E detonation, turning her jump-in into a near-guaranteed one-combo kill on a squishy Seraphine who has no dash to escape the reset threat."},{"when":"Late","text":"With items her passive attack range grows to among the longest in the game and a takedown resets her W, so she jumps in, bursts, and jumps out repeatedly; you survive only by kiting behind frontline and landing Encore before she leaps."}],"wants":{"you":["Max-range Q poke to chip her before she can jump","A support with reliable peel or CC for her W jump-in","Punishing her the moment her W is on cooldown"],"foe":["Landing W-E-auto detonation for a burst all-in","Level 6 Buster Shot to execute and knock away your peel","First-item AD that turns her jump into a one-combo kill"]},"early":"Even at levels 1-2 Tristana's jump threat forces you to play passively; hold max range, shield early, and last-hit carefully because any step forward invites a Rocket Jump all-in you can't escape.","mid":"Through 3-6 she holds the lane with W-E burst and a level-6 execute ult, so your job is to farm safely, poke only when her W is down, and lean on your support to punish her jumps.","late":"Tristana stays ahead into the late game thanks to her enormous attack range and reset-driven mobility; you must Q-poke from the very back, save Encore for when she commits, and let your frontline absorb her jump before you fight.","whys":["Level 1 Tristana's jump threat forces you onto the back foot.","Level 2 her W-E all-in potential keeps the lane in her favour.","At level 3 stacked E detonation out-bursts your immobile trades.","Through 4-5 her jump-reset threat keeps you farming defensively.","At 6 her Buster Shot execute and knockback win the all-in.","At one item her AD spike makes her jump a near-guaranteed kill.","Late her huge range and W resets keep her ahead of you."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"twitch","win":["Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Skill","Twitch","Twitch"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Twitch is a weak early lane bully-target: he has no range advantage and relies on stacking Deadly Venom before Contaminate pays off, so your Q outranges his autos and you can chunk him every time he steps up, denying his poison ramp."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Both hit a teamfight ult: your Encore is an AoE chain-CC, while his Spray and Pray (R) plus Ambush stealth let him reposition and pierce your line, so the level hinges on whether you catch him before he goes invisible and repositions."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Twitch spikes hard at one item because Runaan's or a crit component turns his R into a full-team shred and his stacked E starts bursting you from stealth, flipping the kill threat onto him."},{"when":"Late","text":"With items Twitch's Ambush stealth lets him flank and his Spray and Pray beam melts your whole team from behind cover; you must land Encore or an Oracle-revealed catch on him the instant he emerges, or he shreds you first."}],"wants":{"you":["Poking his weak early ranged trades before he stacks poison","Punishing him at 3-5 while he lacks range and burst","A support with CC to lock him before he can Ambush away"],"foe":["Reaching one item so his R and E shred and burst","Using Ambush stealth to flank and reposition in fights","Stacking Deadly Venom for a big Contaminate payoff"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are yours: Twitch has no early range and needs to stack poison, so hold priority, land Q harass on his last-hits, and shield your support to keep him off the wave.","mid":"Through 3-5 you stay ahead by out-ranging his autos and punishing every step up, but at 6 the lane evens out because his ult and Ambush stealth let him reposition around your Encore.","late":"Once Twitch completes his first item he takes over, his stacked E bursts you and Spray and Pray shreds your backline from stealth, so you rely on vision, peel, and landing Encore the moment he reveals.","whys":["Level 1 Twitch's weak early range lets your Q harass dominate.","Level 2 your poke and shield keep him off the wave and unstacked.","At level 3 you out-range his autos and punish his last-hits.","Through 4-5 your sustained Q poke keeps beating his pre-item kit.","At 6 his ult and Ambush stealth offset your Encore so it's even.","At one item Twitch's R shred and stacked E burst flip the lane.","Late his stealth flanks and Spray and Pray out-damage your team."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"varus","win":["Varus","Varus","Varus","Varus","Varus","Varus","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Varus out-pokes you early: his Piercing Arrow (Q) charges for long-range chunks and his Blighted Quiver (W) stacks amplify each hit, so he can zone you off farm from beyond your Q range while you have no way to punish back."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Chain of Corruption (R) is a point-and-click root that spreads to nearby enemies, giving Varus's lane a guaranteed all-in engage onto your immobile frame; if he lands R and his support follows, you get chain-CC'd and bursted before you can Encore back."},{"when":"1st item","text":"At one item Varus's W stack detonation and Q burst spike hard, letting him melt you or the wave from max range while his ult remains a reliable pick threat, keeping the kill pressure firmly on his side."},{"when":"Late","text":"The lane finally evens late: your Q and Encore match his poke range and your chain-CC answers his R engage, so fights come down to who lands their AoE first rather than a clear Varus edge."}],"wants":{"you":["Reaching late-game where your range and Encore match his poke","Staying behind minions so his Q charge misses","Punishing him while his Q and R are on cooldown"],"foe":["Long-range Q poke with W stacks to zone you off farm","Landing Chain of Corruption R for a guaranteed all-in","One-item W detonation burst from max range"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favour Varus: his charged Q out-ranges your poke and his W stacks let him chunk you whenever you approach the wave, so farm carefully behind minions and dodge his skillshots.","mid":"Through 3-6 Varus holds the lane with poke and a point-and-click R engage that punishes your lack of mobility, so respect his all-in, only trade when his Q is down, and lean on your support to dodge or peel his ult.","late":"By the late game the matchup levels off, your Q and Encore reach as far as his poke and your chain-CC answers his R, turning fights into a skillshot duel where landing your AoE first decides it.","whys":["Level 1 Varus's charged Q out-ranges your early poke.","Level 2 his W-stack harass chunks you off the wave.","At level 3 his poke keeps zoning you while you can't punish back.","Through 4-5 his range and W detonation hold the lane advantage.","At 6 his point-and-click R engage punishes your immobility.","At one item Varus's burst from max range keeps kill pressure his.","Late your matched range and Encore even the fight to skill."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"vayne","win":["Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Vayne","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Your combo of E (Beat Drop) into Q (High Note) plus a Sound-augmented auto shreds Vayne, who has no range and no way to trade back through your poke while she farms with Q Tumble."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Encore's massive AoE root/charm makes Vayne's Q reposition worthless in the 2v2; land it and your support all-in deletes her before Ultimate invisibility can save her."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once Vayne finishes Vayne items and hits three Silver Bolt stacks she starts winning extended fights, so use your first-item burst window before she out-DPSes you."},{"when":"Late","text":"In teamfights Vayne with Q resets and R invisibility will run you down if she reaches you, so hold Encore and E to peel and never let her close the gap."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke her down early so she can never lane bully","Land Encore to catch her out of Tumble range","End fights fast with support CC before Silver Bolts ramp"],"foe":["Stack Silver Bolts on you in a drawn-out duel","Use Q Tumble to dodge your E and reposition","Reach the backline with R invisibility in teamfights"]},"early":"You dominate levels 1-5: your E-Q poke and superior range punish Vayne every time she steps up to CS, and she has no early tools to answer. Zone her off the wave and keep her low.","mid":"Through level 6 you stay ahead because Encore's AoE charm and root set up an all-in Vayne can't escape, while her Q Tumble only dodges one ability. Keep threatening the hard engage.","late":"Once Vayne completes her first item and hits Silver Bolt uptime she flips the matchup, out-DPSing you in extended fights and using R invisibility plus Q resets to chase you down. Kite, peel, and burst her before she ramps.","whys":["You out-range and out-poke Vayne at level 1 with no risk.","Your level 2 E-Q trade chunks a champion with no lane presence.","At level 3 your full combo plus support CC threatens a kill she can't answer.","Levels 4-5 you keep zoning her off farm while she has no trade-back.","Level 6 Encore's AoE charm makes a clean all-in Vayne cannot Tumble out of.","At one item Vayne's Silver Bolts and DPS overtake your poke-based lead.","Late game Vayne's invisibility and Q resets let her run you down in fights."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"veigar","win":["Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Skill","Veigar","Veigar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You out-trade Veigar early: your E-Q poke plus Passive Note stacks let you win short exchanges while his Q (Baleful Strike) is a farm tool and his W (Dark Matter) is slow and easy to sidestep behind minions."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Both of you gain a game-changing ult - your Encore versus his R (Primordial Burst) execute - so it becomes a skill fight over who lands their spell first while dodging the other's."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once Veigar stacks AP and completes his first item his E (Event Horizon) cage plus W burst can one-shot you, so respect his stun range and never walk into the cage."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late-game Veigar with infinite AP scaling deletes you through Encore range if his E lands, so position on the far flank and force him to cage a frontliner instead of you."}],"wants":{"you":["Win short trades early with E-Q before he scales","Sidestep Dark Matter behind minions","Punish him whenever his E cage is on cooldown"],"foe":["Land Event Horizon to lock you for the W-R combo","Stack AP off Baleful Strike last-hits","Reach infinite scaling to one-shot you late"]},"early":"You control levels 1-5 comfortably: Veigar is a scaling mage whose early damage is low, and your E-Q poke plus range let you chunk him every time he steps to farm. Deny his Baleful Strike stacks by shoving and forcing him off the wave.","mid":"At level 6 the lane levels out to a skill matchup - your Encore against his R execute means whoever lands their spell first wins, so it comes down to dodging Dark Matter and Event Horizon.","late":"Once Veigar completes items and stacks AP he becomes the threat, able to cage-and-burst you from range with E into W-R. Play far back in fights, hold your position until his cage is down, and never give him a clean flank angle.","whys":["Level 1 your poke and range beat a scaling mage with no early damage.","Level 2 your E-Q trade wins while his Q is only a farm tool.","Level 3 you out-trade him and can deny Baleful Strike stacks.","Levels 4-5 your range keeps zoning a low-damage Veigar off the wave.","Level 6 it's even - your Encore versus his R execute is a spell-dodging skill fight.","At one item Veigar's AP cage combo can burst you from range.","Late game his infinite AP scaling one-shots you if E lands."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"xayah","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Xayah","Xayah","Xayah"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Early is an even skill lane: your E-Q poke trades with her W (Deadly Plumage) auto-windows, but she can bank Feathers from Q and E to threaten a root, so watch her feather count before committing."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Xayah's R (Featherstorm) gives her invulnerability and a big feather root, out-dueling your Encore in a straight 2v2, so she edges the level-6 all-in unless you catch her before ult."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With her first item Xayah's Bladecaller root plus W attack speed lets her burst you down, so respect her feather setup and don't stand in a line of thrown feathers."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late-game Xayah roots multiple targets with R feathers and cleans up teamfights while untargetable, so stay spread from her feather lines and use Encore to disrupt her before she recalls the storm."}],"wants":{"you":["Trade in the poke windows when her feathers are spent","Land Encore before she pops R invulnerability","Force fights while Bladecaller root is on cooldown"],"foe":["Bank feathers from Q and E for a big Bladecaller root","Pop Featherstorm to dodge your Encore and reset","Root multiple targets in the late teamfight"]},"early":"Levels 1-5 play out as a skill matchup: you can poke with E-Q and she answers with W-empowered autos, so the lane is decided by who tracks feathers and cooldowns better rather than a raw kit advantage. Trade only when her feather bank is low.","mid":"At level 6 Xayah tilts ahead - Featherstorm's invulnerability lets her dodge your Encore and her feather root sets up a clean all-in, so respect her ult timer and don't force the 2v2 into her spike.","late":"With items Xayah's Bladecaller root plus attack-speed steroid out-DPSes you and her R makes her untargetable in fights while she roots your whole side. Position wide of her feather lines, hold Encore to interrupt, and never duel her head-on.","whys":["Level 1 is even - your poke and her feather setup cancel out.","Level 2 the trade is a skill fight over feather tracking.","Level 3 neither kit dominates; cooldown discipline decides it.","Levels 4-5 stay even as you poke and she banks feathers.","Level 6 Featherstorm's invulnerability and root beat your Encore all-in.","At one item her Bladecaller root and attack speed out-burst you.","Late game she roots multiple targets and cleans up while untargetable."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"zeri","win":["Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Skill","Zeri","Zeri"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You beat Zeri early: her Q (Burst Fire) does chip damage and she is squishy with no escape until R, so your E-Q poke plus Note-empowered autos win every trade before she scales."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Both ults arrive - your Encore charm versus her R (Lightning Crash) - making it an even skill fight, though her ult grants move speed and wall-dashes to dodge your Encore if you telegraph it."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once Zeri completes her first item her Q scales with AP/crit and her W plus E wall-dash kiting let her out-DPS and out-maneuver you, so burst her in your item window before she snowballs."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late-game Zeri is a hyper-mobile kiter who resets speed off her ult and dashes over every wall, so she is nearly impossible to pin - hold Encore to catch her mid-dash or she runs you down in fights."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke her low with E-Q before she scales","All-in while she has no escape pre-6","Land Encore to lock a slippery target"],"foe":["Scale her Q with first-item AP and crit","Kite with E wall-dash and W after level 6","Reset move speed off Lightning Crash to run you down"]},"early":"Levels 1-5 are yours: Zeri is a weak-laning scaler whose Q only chips and who has no dash to escape your poke until 6. Punish her hard with E-Q trades and threaten the all-in whenever she steps up to farm.","mid":"At level 6 it evens out - your Encore charm against her Lightning Crash is a skill fight, and her ult's move speed plus E wall-dash can dodge your engage if you show it early. Bait her ult or land Encore cleanly.","late":"After her first item Zeri flips the matchup, scaling her Q with AP and crit and kiting you endlessly with W and wall-dashes while her R resets her speed. Use your item-spike burst window early, and late game hold Encore to catch her in a dash or she out-maneuvers you every fight.","whys":["Level 1 you out-poke a weak-early scaler with no escape.","Level 2 your E-Q trade beats her chip-damage Q.","Level 3 you can all-in a Zeri who has no dash to answer.","Levels 4-5 you keep zoning her off farm before she scales.","Level 6 it's even - Encore charm versus Lightning Crash is a skill fight.","At one item Zeri's scaling Q and wall-dash kiting out-DPS you.","Late game her mobility and speed resets let her run you down."]},
  {"a":"seraphine_bot","b":"ziggs","win":["Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Skill","Skill","Seraphine"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ziggs out-pokes you early: his Q (Bouncing Bomb) has more range and bounces over minions to hit you at the CS line, so you take unfavorable poke trades and struggle to farm under his zone."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"The lane evens at 6 - his R (Mega Inferno Bomb) is a wave-clear and long-range poke ult while your Encore is a hard engage, so it becomes a skill fight over spacing and dodging his Q bounces."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Both spike at one item but it stays even: he zones with W (Satchel) and Q poke, you look to close distance and land Encore, so respect his Satchel knockback that cancels your engage."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late-game you overtake Ziggs - in teamfights your Encore AoE charm reaches his backline mage position and locks him down, and once you gap-close he has only Satchel to escape your all-in."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Q bounces behind the caster minions","Close the gap and land Encore in fights","Punish him once his Satchel is on cooldown"],"foe":["Zone your farm with long-range Q poke","Satchel-knockback you out of engage range","Chip you down before you can close distance"]},"early":"Levels 1-5 belong to Ziggs: his Bouncing Bomb out-ranges your E-Q and bounces over the minion wall to poke you off the CS line, so you eat chip damage and farm cautiously. Use minions to body-block his Q and don't over-extend into his zone.","mid":"At level 6 the lane levels out - his Mega Inferno Bomb gives him long-range ult poke and wave-clear while your Encore is a hard engage, making it a spacing and dodging skill fight. Look for a moment his Satchel is down to threaten the all-in.","late":"Late game you take over: your Encore's AoE charm reaches Ziggs where he sits in the backline and locks him for your team, and after you gap-close he has only Satchel knockback to survive your burst. Force teamfights where you can flank onto him.","whys":["Level 1 Ziggs out-ranges your poke with Bouncing Bomb.","Level 2 his Q bounces over minions to zone your farm.","Level 3 you keep eating unfavorable long-range poke trades.","Levels 4-5 he controls the lane with superior Q range.","Level 6 it evens - his R poke versus your Encore engage is a skill fight.","At one item it stays even as he zones and you seek to close distance.","Late game your Encore charm reaches his backline and locks him for the kill."]}
